{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_23","type":"agent_message","text":"{\"reviewer\":\"codex\",\"schemaVersion\":1,\"scores\":null,\"weightedTotal\":null,\"verdict\":\"FAIL\",\"issues\":[{\"severity\":\"P1\",\"location\":\"server/handlers/enforce.ts:97\",\"description\":\"ban/kick emits space:error but leaves the target sockets fully authorized until the 250ms delayed disconnect. During that window the socket still has socket.data.spaceId, role, and restriction unchanged, so a malicious client can keep sending chat/admin/editor/media events; existing handlers authorize from those cached fields and do not re-check the DB.\",\"recommendation\":\"Revoke server-side state synchronously before the grace delay: mark the socket as no longer in-space, downgrade role/restriction, leave the room or run presence cleanup immediately, and make handlers reject revoked sockets. Then delay only the physical disconnect so the error packet can flush.\",\"defer\":false,\"deferRationale\":null,\"fixNow\":true},{\"severity\":\"P2\",\"location\":\"server/handlers/enforce.ts:97\",\"description\":\"Multi-tab ban/kick schedules disconnect for every socket, and each disconnect runs leaveSpace, which deletes the same userId and emits player:left. That produces duplicate player:left events and can also remove presence as soon as the first tab disconnects, before the remaining tab disconnect handlers run.\",\"recommendation\":\"Make presence cleanup user-scoped rather than socket-count blind: either disconnect/cleanup once per user or have leaveSpace emit player:left only when no remaining socket for that user is still in the space room.\",\"defer\":false,\"deferRationale\":null,\"fixNow\":false},{\"severity\":\"P3\",\"location\":\"server/handlers/enforce.ts:154\",\"description\":\"The body limit is documented as bytes, but enforcement accumulates Buffer chunks into a string and checks raw.length. Multi-byte UTF-8 bodies can exceed 4096 bytes while staying under the character count, so the limit is not exact.\",\"recommendation\":\"Track byte length from Buffer.byteLength/chunk.length while collecting the body, and reject when accumulated bytes exceed ENFORCE_MAX_BODY_BYTES.\",\"defer\":true,\"deferRationale\":\"The endpoint is HMAC-protected and the practical bypass is small, so this is hardening rather than an immediate functional blocker.\",\"fixNow\":false}]}"}}
